# Maintaining docs/theory/

> High-level principles: `docs/design/agent_instructions_design.md`

`docs/theory/` contains **mathematical derivations** in reStructuredText (`.rst`)
format, based on [Shi2016]. These are the formal mathematical foundations for
the distributions and algorithms implemented in normix.

## Current Contents

| File | Topic |
|---|---|
| `gig.rst` | Generalized Inverse Gaussian distribution |
| `gh.rst` | Generalized Hyperbolic distribution |
| `em_algorithm.rst` | EM algorithm for GH mixtures |
| `shrinkage.rst` | Shrinkage estimation |
| `factor_analysis.rst` | Factor analysis |
| `online_em.rst` | Online EM algorithm |
| `mean_risk_optimization.rst` | Mean-risk portfolio optimization |
| `cvar_derivatives.rst` | CVaR derivatives |
| `transaction_costs.rst` | Transaction cost modeling |
| `enb.rst` | Effective number of bets |
| `generalized_enb.rst` | Generalized ENB |

## Format

- **reStructuredText** (`.rst`) — not Markdown. Use `.. math::` directives for equations.
- Follow the conventions in existing files for consistency.
- `index.rst` maintains the table of contents via `.. toctree::`.

## When to Update

- **New distribution added**: add a theory file with its mathematical derivation
- **New algorithm implemented** (e.g. new EM variant, new optimization): add derivation
- **Error found in derivation**: fix in place, note the correction

## When to Create a New File

1. Check `index.rst` — does a relevant file already exist?
2. Add the new file to the `.. toctree::` in `index.rst`
3. Follow the structure of existing files (definitions, properties, proofs)

## Relationship to Other Docs

- `docs/theory/` = **formal math** (definitions, theorems, proofs)
- `docs/tech_notes/` = **implementation notes** (benchmarks, numerical issues, algorithm choices)
- `docs/design/` = **design rationale** (why we chose this approach)

These three are complementary. A theory file derives the formula; a tech note
explains how we compute it efficiently; a design doc explains why we chose that
computation over alternatives.

## Gotchas

- **Don't put implementation details here.** This is pure math. Code patterns belong in `.cursor/rules/` or tech notes.
- **Don't mix `.rst` and `.md`** in this directory. All theory docs are `.rst`.
- **Reference [Shi2016] properly** using the `.. [Shi2016]` citation defined in `index.rst`.
